=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Guides_UGens-and-Synths_ex5 ===

DESCRIPTION: A dark pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 800 Hz, featuring punchy attack and sustained envelope, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: dark
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: stable
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 800.0000
  harmonic_decay_rate: -15.9874
  harmonic_regularity: 0.5007
  pitch_clarity: 101.4522
  inharmonicity: 0.0000
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -3.7276
  resonance_freq: 796.7285

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Unit Generators and Synths Example 5
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Guides/UGens-and-Synths.html
// Tags: UGens-and-Synths, Guides
// ---
// --- Example 5 ---
{ FSinOsc.ar(800, 0, 0.2) }.play; // create and play a sine oscillator at 800 Hz
